SysManage Agent is a lightweight, secure, cross-platform system management
daemon that connects to the SysManage server via WebSocket for real-time
remote management.

Features:
  * Real-time WebSocket communication (TLS, optional mTLS)
  * System inventory and metrics (CPU, memory, disk, network)
  * Package management and update orchestration
  * Remote command execution with audit logging
  * Firewall / antivirus / certificate management hooks
  * Declarative deployment plans driven by the SysManage server

The agent runs as a background service and requires no inbound network
ports.  All communication is initiated by the agent to the server,
simplifying firewall configuration.
